\fs24
\b IH35 ERP — Recommended Report Catalog\b0\par
\par
Goal: mirror the most useful reporting patterns from \b QuickBooks Online (QBO)\b0\ and \b Samsara\b0\ while staying practical for fleet operations (dispatch, shop, accounting).\par
\par
\b Standard filters for every report\b0\par
\pard\li360
\b Date range\b0: from/to (default presets: last 7 / 30 / 90 / YTD)\par
\b Unit filters\b0: Trucks / Trailers / Company vehicles; single unit; multi-select\par
\b Vendor filters\b0: single vendor; vendor group (fuel vs repair shops)\par
\b Source filters\b0: Maintenance records vs Work orders vs AP vs Fuel imports vs Bill payments\par
\b Export\b0: CSV (and PDF for printable ops)\par
\pard\li0
\par
\b A) Maintenance / Shop reports\b0\par
\pard\li360
\b 1. Maintenance detailed (records + cost breakdown)\b0\par
Each maintenance record with full cost lines; show part positions (tires/batteries/etc.) with position + part reference.\par
Filters: date range, unit, record type (maintenance/repair/tire/accident), vendor.\par
\par
\b 2. Maintenance spend by unit\b0\par
Total spend per unit, with counts, avg cost, and last service date.\par
Analog: QBO “Expenses by Vendor” pattern but by asset.\par
\par
\b 3. Repairs only (count + cost)\b0\par
Only recordType=repair; totals by unit, vendor, service type.\par
\par
\b 4. Tires / position-based parts report\b0\par
All tire/battery/etc lines with position, install/remove mileage (when available), cost, vendor, and unit.\par
\par
\b 5. Internal shop vs External shop vs Roadside\b0\par
Totals and detailed lists by repair location; highlight overdue jobs and bottlenecks.\par
\par
\b 6. Shop queue throughput\b0\par
Awaiting/In progress/Completed counts; average cycle time; overdue list with reason codes.\par
\pard\li0
\par
\b B) Fuel / Diesel reports\b0\par
\pard\li360
\b 1. Fuel purchases (detailed)\b0\par
Each purchase: date, unit, vendor, location, gallons, total, price/gal, odometer.\par
\par
\b 2. Fuel spend by unit\b0\par
Total gallons + total spend + avg price/gal by unit; optional MPG estimates if miles exist.\par
\par
\b 3. Fuel spend by vendor/location\b0\par
Identify high-cost stations, fraud patterns, and pricing outliers.\par
\par
\b 4. Fuel anomalies\b0\par
Mismatch: gallons vs expected miles, sudden spikes, missing odometer, repeated same-day fills.\par
Analog: Samsara fuel/usage exception style + internal heuristics.\par
\pard\li0
\par
\b C) Safety / Driver compliance reports\b0\par
\pard\li360
\b 1. Driver files compliance\b0\par
Expiring/missing: CDL, med card, drug test, hire date; “due soon” rollups.\par
\par
\b 2. Incident / accident cost rollup\b0\par
Accident records and related expenses; totals by driver/unit/time window.\par
\pard\li0
\par
\b D) Tracking / Fleet utilization reports\b0\par
\pard\li360
\b 1. Idle / revenue at risk snapshot (time-window)\b0\par
Units likely idle, last completed load age, distance-to-yard, and estimated revenue at risk.\par
\par
\b 2. Operational status timeline\b0\par
In shop/OOS vs active, by unit, over date range.\par
\pard\li0
\par
\b E) Accounting / QBO-aligned reports\b0\par
\pard\li360
\b 1. Unpaid bills (AP aging)\b0\par
Open bills by vendor with aging buckets.\par
Analog: QBO “Unpaid Bills” + “Vendor Balance Summary/Detail”.\par
\par
\b 2. Bill payment list (this app)\b0\par
All BillPayments created by the ERP with audit trail and reversal status.\par
Analog: QBO “Bill Payment List”.\par
\par
\b 3. Purchases/expenses list (posted by ERP)\b0\par
Purchases (expenses) and Bills created by the ERP; filter by vendor/category/unit/date.\par
\par
\b 4. Expense by category (7/30/90 + compare)\b0\par
Totals by expense category with % deltas vs prior period.\par
Analog: QBO “Profit and Loss” drill patterns (expense lines).\par
\par
\b 5. Audit / change log (ERP)\b0\par
Who created/posted/reverted transactions and when.\par
Analog: QBO “Audit Log”.\par
\pard\li0
\par
\b F) Compliance (IFTA + ops)\b0\par
\pard\li360
\b 1. IFTA prep summary\b0\par
Miles by jurisdiction (when available), fuel gallons by state, and exceptions.\par
\par
\b 2. Maintenance compliance\b0\par
PM completion rates, overdue services by unit, and upcoming PM schedule.\par
\pard\li0
\par
\b Implementation approach\b0\par
\pard\li360
Phase 1: Maintenance detailed + Fuel purchases + Unpaid bills + Bill payment list + Shop throughput.\par
Phase 2: Tires/parts position report + anomaly detection + AP aging + audit log.\par
Phase 3: IFTA/jurisdiction reporting once mileage-by-state data is reliable.\par
\pard\li0
\par
End of document.\par
}
